Full Description: Rubicon is working with a Private Equity fund for project finance and is looking to raise the capital required for remaining due diligence including legal and engineering.     Rubicon Energy LLC (Rubicon) is a limited liability company in the business of crude gathering, marketing and transportation. (http://www.rubiconnrg.com/) founded in 2013. The initial business focus for Rubicon was crude gathering and marketing in the Bakken play of North Dakota. Rubicon has a relationship with Vermillion Asset Management, a subsidiary of the Carlyle Group, who is the liquidity provider for the physical commodity purchases. Rubicon operates primarily in the mid-stream sector of various shale oil plays and related US crude production to market domestically produced crude, leveraging relationships with producers and refiners. Rubicon is currently focusing capital on the acquisition of key assets to provide sustained physical commodity trading opportunities. The main areas for acquisition are in the transportation sector, mid-stream, origination and marketing for crude oil, NGL liquids, and refined products. Rubicon approaches its trading activity of crude and products actively managing price risk and volatility: Rubicon trades with an underlying physical position in the commodity and then matches producers with refiners, and refiners with end users. Rubicon does not speculate in oil futures contracts but concentrates on the fundamentals of the trade to satisfy the needs of the buyers and the sellers. Rubicon has expanded its operations into the product markets to supply heavy fuel oil, diesel, gasoline, jet, and asphalt products to its clients in the US, Dominican Republic and other Caribbean/central American locations.
